# Spotify Web API Configuration
# Follow these steps to get your Spotify Client ID:
#
# 1. Go to https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
# 2. Log in with your Spotify account
# 3. Click "Create app"
# 4. Fill in the app details:
#    - App name: "Sounds Expensive Mix Analyzer" (or any name you prefer)
#    - App description: "Audio analysis tool for music production"
#    - Redirect URI: https://trentbecknell.github.io/soundsexpensive/
#                     (or http://localhost:5173/ for local development)
# 5. Accept the Terms of Service
# 6. Click "Settings" on your app dashboard
# 7. Copy your "Client ID" and paste it below

VITE_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_spotify_client_id_here

# Note: This app uses OAuth 2.0 PKCE flow, which doesn't require a client secret
# PKCE is more secure for client-side applications

# For local development, make sure to add http://localhost:5173/ as a redirect URI
# For production, use https://trentbecknell.github.io/soundsexpensive/
